1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:40,000
(Watch on www.kisskh.li Support Admin)

2
00:00:42,647 --> 00:00:46,067
SOLD OUT ON YOU

3
00:01:05,003 --> 00:01:05,837
Fine.

4
00:01:08,631 --> 00:01:11,301
I'm in Deokpung,
so I should follow their stupid rules.

5
00:01:12,552 --> 00:01:13,803
I'll reverse my car then.

6
00:01:24,480 --> 00:01:26,149
What was that? What happened?

7
00:01:32,655 --> 00:01:34,616
Hey, what's going on?

8
00:01:36,826 --> 00:01:39,954
Stop pressing that!
Can't you see I'm trying to move?

9
00:01:41,164 --> 00:01:42,707
What's with him?

10
00:01:48,880 --> 00:01:50,298
I can't believe this.

11
00:02:16,699 --> 00:02:17,784
Aren't you moving your car?

12
00:02:17,867 --> 00:02:19,535
I'm sure you can squeeze through.

13
00:02:20,245 --> 00:02:21,663
You can't just leave like this.

14
00:02:23,748 --> 00:02:26,000
I'm in a hurry right now,

15
00:02:26,584 --> 00:02:28,795
so hit or push through my car if you want.

16
00:02:30,755 --> 00:02:32,006
Oh, right.

17
00:02:33,049 --> 00:02:34,092
My car's pretty expensive.

18
00:02:35,176 --> 00:02:36,511
You should keep that in mind.

19
00:02:39,055 --> 00:02:39,889
Excuse me.

20
00:02:41,057 --> 00:02:41,933
Excuse me!

21
00:02:42,850 --> 00:02:45,061
Where's the mushroom farm?

22
00:04:10,063 --> 00:04:12,565
Where in the world is it?

23
00:04:22,533 --> 00:04:24,285
Walking like this is a bit better.

24
00:04:24,952 --> 00:04:27,288
Damn it.
Why did they want me to sell these?

25
00:04:27,372 --> 00:04:29,999
Geez, my feet are aching.

26
00:04:42,887 --> 00:04:44,347
Why are you following me?

27
00:04:45,181 --> 00:04:47,016
-What?
-Why are you following me?

28
00:04:47,100 --> 00:04:48,309
I'm just headed this way.

29
00:04:54,649 --> 00:04:57,110
I think he really is following me.

30
00:04:58,945 --> 00:05:00,029
Damn it.

31
00:05:21,092 --> 00:05:22,844
You really are following me.

32
00:05:23,845 --> 00:05:25,721
I'm just passing by.

33
00:05:25,805 --> 00:05:27,432
I can't believe it.

34
00:05:27,515 --> 00:05:29,892
I've had men follow me
in their sports cars before,

35
00:05:29,976 --> 00:05:32,520
but a tractor is a first.

36
00:05:32,603 --> 00:05:33,938
I'll admit it's pretty unique.

37
00:05:34,647 --> 00:05:36,107
But, sir,

38
00:05:36,190 --> 00:05:39,026
I'm really here
to just meet someone important.

39
00:05:39,110 --> 00:05:42,697
So, please don't bother me anymore.
I'm asking you very nicely.

40
00:05:44,949 --> 00:05:46,909
-Excuse me.
-Geez, please stop.

41
00:05:47,952 --> 00:05:49,996
Wait, this is good. Let me ask you.

42
00:05:50,079 --> 00:05:52,123
-Do you know where the mushroom farm is?
-Excuse me.

43
00:05:52,206 --> 00:05:54,125
They're white flower noori mushrooms.

44
00:05:58,629 --> 00:06:00,715
Over there? Where?

45
00:06:00,798 --> 00:06:02,884
Move over there so I can pass by!

46
00:06:05,595 --> 00:06:06,929
What… Oh, my gosh!

47
00:06:10,558 --> 00:06:11,392
What the…

48
00:06:12,143 --> 00:06:14,437
Is he out of his mind?

49
00:06:14,520 --> 00:06:16,147
Excuse me! Hey!

50
00:06:20,735 --> 00:06:22,153
The mushrooms!

51
00:06:22,236 --> 00:06:23,779
The white flower noori mushrooms!

52
00:06:24,322 --> 00:06:25,656
Excuse me! Sir!

53
00:06:26,157 --> 00:06:28,075
Just a moment, sir!

54
00:06:28,159 --> 00:06:30,453
Sir, let me just look…

55
00:06:39,879 --> 00:06:41,547
So it can reverse!

56
00:06:42,381 --> 00:06:43,466
Damn it.

57
00:06:45,384 --> 00:06:48,596
Hey, you said earlier
your tractor couldn't reverse.

58
00:06:50,431 --> 00:06:52,433
-What do you want?
-Well…

59
00:06:52,516 --> 00:06:55,311
This seems like the mushroom farm.
Is the owner inside--

60
00:06:55,394 --> 00:06:56,395
No.

61
00:06:57,605 --> 00:06:58,564
Excuse me.

62
00:06:58,648 --> 00:07:00,524
You didn't even check
if the owner is inside.

63
00:07:00,608 --> 00:07:03,069
If he was, this wouldn't be happening.

64
00:07:03,152 --> 00:07:03,986
What?

65
00:07:05,196 --> 00:07:06,656
When will the owner come then?

66
00:07:06,739 --> 00:07:08,699
-He won't be here for a while.
-What?

67
00:07:10,409 --> 00:07:11,786
-Hey.
-In that case,

68
00:07:11,869 --> 00:07:14,080
could you please contact him for me?

69
00:07:15,915 --> 00:07:17,917
Fine. I'll tell him

70
00:07:19,126 --> 00:07:22,296
that someone extremely rude
just barged in here.

71
00:07:22,380 --> 00:07:24,715
Well, it was my first time here, so…

72
00:07:24,799 --> 00:07:25,883
By the way,

73
00:07:25,967 --> 00:07:27,343
he hates people like that.

74
00:07:29,303 --> 00:07:30,805
I haven't introduced myself.

75
00:07:32,932 --> 00:07:35,393
I'm a home shopping host
from HIT Homeshopping.

76
00:07:35,476 --> 00:07:37,186
My name's Dam Ye-jin.

77
00:07:42,733 --> 00:07:44,610
HIT HOMESHOPPING
HOME SHOPPING HOST DAM YE-JIN

78
00:07:50,616 --> 00:07:51,784
What? What is he doing?

79
00:07:54,662 --> 00:07:55,496
Excuse me.

80
00:07:57,790 --> 00:07:59,125
Where are you going?

81
00:08:00,084 --> 00:08:01,002
What is that?

82
00:08:01,586 --> 00:08:02,420
What?

83
00:08:07,592 --> 00:08:08,634
Sir…

84
00:08:10,678 --> 00:08:12,179
I can't believe this guy.

85
00:08:16,058 --> 00:08:16,892
Geez!

86
00:08:17,893 --> 00:08:24,650
Time will solve everything

87
00:08:52,678 --> 00:08:54,639
It's a bit dry today,
so spray a lot of water.

88
00:08:55,222 --> 00:08:56,974
-All right.
-There we go.

89
00:08:57,058 --> 00:08:57,933
A bit more gently.

90
00:08:58,017 --> 00:08:59,352
Okay.

91
00:09:08,527 --> 00:09:09,528
Mr. Park.

92
00:09:13,032 --> 00:09:14,784
Hey, Mechoori.

93
00:09:14,867 --> 00:09:16,369
You came back so quickly.

94
00:09:16,452 --> 00:09:18,412
You didn't load a box of mushrooms.

95
00:09:19,330 --> 00:09:21,290
Gosh, I must have forgotten it.

96
00:09:21,374 --> 00:09:24,585
Didn't I tell you to just focus on work?

97
00:09:24,669 --> 00:09:27,296
As the supervisor,
you're supposed to oversee those things.

98
00:09:27,380 --> 00:09:30,007
I just played a bit of music
to keep our energy up.

99
00:09:31,050 --> 00:09:32,635
Kwang-mo got caught red-handed.

100
00:09:32,718 --> 00:09:33,761
I knew he would.

101
00:09:34,428 --> 00:09:36,847
It boosts metabolism
and is an effective pest control--

102
00:09:36,931 --> 00:09:37,848
Mr. Park.

103
00:09:38,641 --> 00:09:40,976
This will be used to make
medicine and makeup products.

104
00:09:41,477 --> 00:09:43,813
Slacking off like that
is detrimental here.

105
00:09:45,815 --> 00:09:47,400
I'll be careful from now on.

106
00:09:47,483 --> 00:09:48,734
Power on.

107
00:09:48,818 --> 00:09:51,195
I'm sorry

108
00:09:54,490 --> 00:09:57,410
This is the last time
I'm letting this slide.

109
00:10:01,831 --> 00:10:02,790
Sorry.

110
00:10:03,374 --> 00:10:04,458
I'm sorry…

111
00:10:04,542 --> 00:10:05,626
Mr. Park!

112
00:10:08,921 --> 00:10:12,091
Oh, my gosh! These are the white flower
noori mushrooms, right?

113
00:10:12,633 --> 00:10:14,218
-You're still here?
-I was about to go.

114
00:10:14,969 --> 00:10:16,929
But do you have
any leftover slippers here?

115
00:10:17,012 --> 00:10:18,389
I'll pay full price for them.

116
00:10:18,472 --> 00:10:19,390
No.

117
00:10:19,473 --> 00:10:20,975
Don't be like that. Just help me out.

118
00:10:21,058 --> 00:10:24,019
I can't take another step in these heels.

119
00:10:27,982 --> 00:10:31,068
You can't possibly make me
keep walking in this condition, can you?

120
00:10:31,152 --> 00:10:32,486
Please.

121
00:10:37,283 --> 00:10:38,951
Then, at least give me some plastic bags…

122
00:10:39,535 --> 00:10:41,162
Why did you run in those heels anyway?

123
00:10:41,245 --> 00:10:45,458
I couldn't let my chance
to meet the farm owner slip away.

124
00:10:45,541 --> 00:10:47,126
Even if I broke my toes, I had to run.

125
00:10:53,299 --> 00:10:54,675
Follow me.

126
00:11:00,723 --> 00:11:02,975
No need to pay. Just take a pair of these.

127
00:11:04,810 --> 00:11:06,395
If you keep loitering,

128
00:11:06,479 --> 00:11:08,230
I'll report you for obstructing business.

129
00:11:13,694 --> 00:11:14,945
There's more in here.

130
00:11:17,114 --> 00:11:18,157
But…

131
00:11:18,657 --> 00:11:20,034
There's nothing I can wear…

132
00:11:22,369 --> 00:11:23,204
Geez…

133
00:11:31,712 --> 00:11:32,630
Damn it.

134
00:11:33,589 --> 00:11:35,633
How do they expect me to wear these?

135
00:11:51,273 --> 00:11:52,483
I'm Dam Ye-jin.

136
00:11:53,484 --> 00:11:56,028
I don't back out
once I've made up my mind.

137
00:12:03,369 --> 00:12:04,203
What?

138
00:12:05,287 --> 00:12:06,622
What are they doing?

139
00:12:11,627 --> 00:12:15,381
Are they stealing stuff?

140
00:12:17,258 --> 00:12:19,093
All right, then.

141
00:12:19,927 --> 00:12:21,720
Try anything funny,

142
00:12:21,804 --> 00:12:23,973
and I'll tell on you to the owner.

143
00:12:28,978 --> 00:12:30,396
Pop, pop

144
00:12:31,605 --> 00:12:33,065
Twirling

145
00:12:35,025 --> 00:12:36,694
All done.

146
00:12:36,777 --> 00:12:38,237
Mr. Park. Wait.

147
00:12:41,198 --> 00:12:42,032
What?

148
00:12:47,037 --> 00:12:48,539
There's still a lot left in here.

149
00:12:48,622 --> 00:12:50,082
You have to remove them cleanly.

150
00:12:51,041 --> 00:12:53,794
It's okay to miss one or two.

151
00:12:53,877 --> 00:12:54,878
Mr. Park.

152
00:12:55,421 --> 00:12:57,715
Those one or two you miss will cause mold

153
00:12:57,798 --> 00:12:59,300
and ruin a whole substrate.

154
00:13:00,759 --> 00:13:01,760
Yes, sir.

155
00:13:09,685 --> 00:13:11,353
I have to head back,

156
00:13:11,437 --> 00:13:13,981
so make sure to clean these out properly.

157
00:13:15,190 --> 00:13:16,191
But there's so much…

158
00:13:16,775 --> 00:13:18,027
What?

159
00:13:29,330 --> 00:13:30,414
Rose.

160
00:13:30,998 --> 00:13:34,293
My dear Rose. I missed you so much!

161
00:13:34,918 --> 00:13:36,170
Let's head back to Seoul--

162
00:13:39,673 --> 00:13:40,883
What happened to your ear?

163
00:13:40,966 --> 00:13:42,468
Who did this to you?

164
00:13:42,551 --> 00:13:43,719
No way!

165
00:13:44,345 --> 00:13:45,679
You can't just leave like this.

166
00:13:45,763 --> 00:13:48,307
Hit or push through my car if you want.

167
00:13:48,390 --> 00:13:49,391
Excuse me.

168
00:13:50,309 --> 00:13:51,769
That tractor!

169
00:13:52,353 --> 00:13:54,271
He actually hit my car?

170
00:13:55,648 --> 00:13:57,483
This is totally…

171
00:13:57,566 --> 00:13:59,360
That lunatic!

172
00:14:04,198 --> 00:14:05,824
Hurry up and move your car.

173
00:14:08,452 --> 00:14:11,288
Do you know how busy farmers are?
Don't block the darn road.

174
00:14:11,872 --> 00:14:14,249
And it's so hot today. Come on.

175
00:14:14,333 --> 00:14:15,292
Hurry up and move!

176
00:14:18,629 --> 00:14:19,797
Right.

177
00:14:20,339 --> 00:14:22,716
It's not the only tractor around here.

178
00:14:22,800 --> 00:14:25,052
I'm the crazy fool
for leaving my car here.

179
00:14:26,136 --> 00:14:30,057
I didn't even get to see the owner,
and I only met a crazy jerk.

180
00:14:40,693 --> 00:14:42,945
I'm a home shopping host
from HIT Homeshopping.

181
00:14:43,028 --> 00:14:44,530
My name's Dam Ye-jin.

182
00:14:48,033 --> 00:14:48,867
Mechoori?

183
00:14:49,785 --> 00:14:51,078
Hey, Mechoori.

184
00:14:51,996 --> 00:14:53,080
What's he doing?

185
00:14:53,163 --> 00:14:54,206
Hey, Boss!

186
00:14:54,707 --> 00:14:56,083
What has you so deep in thought?

187
00:14:57,376 --> 00:14:58,502
It's nothing.

188
00:14:58,585 --> 00:14:59,586
Come here.

189
00:15:08,178 --> 00:15:09,596
CHANGSIK
HE DOESN'T BITE

190
00:15:11,557 --> 00:15:12,683
Changsik.

191
00:15:20,024 --> 00:15:21,358
Mechoori!

192
00:15:23,444 --> 00:15:25,237
-Mechoori!
-Hey, Sang-geum!

193
00:15:26,405 --> 00:15:27,573
Mechoori.

194
00:15:30,159 --> 00:15:31,201
Som-yi.

195
00:15:31,285 --> 00:15:33,162
What are you doing here?
What about school?

196
00:15:33,245 --> 00:15:35,914
Don't tell my sister.

197
00:15:35,998 --> 00:15:36,832
No.

198
00:15:36,915 --> 00:15:38,542
You're in trouble now.

199
00:15:38,625 --> 00:15:40,544
You know what Mechoori's like.

200
00:15:40,627 --> 00:15:43,547
Geez. Fine, I'll go.

201
00:15:43,630 --> 00:15:48,218
Gosh, you happened to come
just in time for me to go to the market.

202
00:15:48,302 --> 00:15:51,305
Geez, Mechoori came
at this time on purpose.

203
00:15:51,972 --> 00:15:52,973
I was just passing by.

204
00:15:53,057 --> 00:15:54,475
You always give her a ride.

205
00:15:55,642 --> 00:15:57,394
-Som-yi.
-Okay, I'm leaving.

206
00:16:01,106 --> 00:16:03,358
-I'm only taking you up to the main road.
-All right.

207
00:16:07,571 --> 00:16:09,865
Hello, I'm at the entrance
of Deokpung Village.

208
00:16:09,948 --> 00:16:12,326
My rear wheel's stuck,
and my side mirror's been smashed.

209
00:16:12,409 --> 00:16:13,494
So I can't move.

210
00:16:13,577 --> 00:16:15,913
What? It takes three hours?

211
00:16:15,996 --> 00:16:17,748
I have a live show to do this evening.

212
00:16:17,831 --> 00:16:19,833
I'm a host on TV.

213
00:16:22,419 --> 00:16:24,171
All right, then…

214
00:16:26,215 --> 00:16:27,424
Think, Ye-jin.

215
00:16:27,508 --> 00:16:30,135
You have to get back to Seoul
in four hours.

216
00:16:31,261 --> 00:16:32,971
The bus! Right.

217
00:16:33,055 --> 00:16:34,765
From Deokpung Village, Anyoung-gun…

218
00:16:34,848 --> 00:16:36,183
ANYOUNG-GUN, SEOUL

219
00:16:36,266 --> 00:16:38,268
The bus to Seoul…

220
00:16:39,061 --> 00:16:40,104
STANDARD FARE 19,000 WON

221
00:16:40,187 --> 00:16:41,396
I can take the 2:30 p.m. one.

222
00:16:41,980 --> 00:16:43,190
There's only 30 minutes left?

223
00:16:50,781 --> 00:16:51,782
No way.

224
00:18:16,325 --> 00:18:17,701
Wait, stop!

225
00:18:20,412 --> 00:18:21,747
Excuse me!

226
00:18:22,414 --> 00:18:23,707
Hey!

227
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:26,793
It's so breezy and nice.

228
00:18:26,877 --> 00:18:27,794
-So nice.
-Exactly.

229
00:18:29,171 --> 00:18:30,214
Hey!

230
00:18:30,297 --> 00:18:31,715
Wait!

231
00:18:32,883 --> 00:18:34,051
Look at those clouds.

232
00:18:34,134 --> 00:18:35,844
My goodness!

233
00:18:35,928 --> 00:18:37,512
They're so beautiful!

234
00:18:49,399 --> 00:18:50,734
Wait!

235
00:18:53,403 --> 00:18:54,279
Hey!

236
00:18:54,363 --> 00:18:57,032
Can you please give me a ride
to the bus terminal?

237
00:18:58,909 --> 00:18:59,743
Hey…

238
00:19:10,837 --> 00:19:13,382
Hey! Stop!

239
00:19:13,465 --> 00:19:15,259
-Mechoori!
-Oh, my.

240
00:19:16,343 --> 00:19:18,720
Pull over, Mechoori!

241
00:19:18,804 --> 00:19:20,222
Hey, come on!

242
00:19:20,305 --> 00:19:22,266
My goodness!

243
00:19:22,349 --> 00:19:24,101
I said pull over!

244
00:19:24,184 --> 00:19:26,186
-What do we do?
-Oh, my.

245
00:19:36,947 --> 00:19:38,365
That hurts.

246
00:20:00,345 --> 00:20:01,638
What do you want with that?

247
00:20:02,681 --> 00:20:03,682
What?

248
00:20:06,727 --> 00:20:08,061
It was just sticking out.

249
00:20:19,448 --> 00:20:20,991
Are you all right?

250
00:20:21,074 --> 00:20:22,284
Yes, I'm fine.

251
00:20:22,367 --> 00:20:23,869
-Goodness.
-You're not hurt anywhere?

252
00:20:23,952 --> 00:20:25,162
You're so pretty.

253
00:20:25,746 --> 00:20:26,747
Thank you.

254
00:20:27,456 --> 00:20:28,582
Ma'am.

255
00:20:28,665 --> 00:20:30,208
The bus terminal…

256
00:20:30,292 --> 00:20:31,501
Is it far from here?

257
00:20:32,127 --> 00:20:34,087
It'll take no time
when you get on the bus.

258
00:20:34,921 --> 00:20:36,256
That's a relief. Thank you.

259
00:20:37,382 --> 00:20:38,675
Gosh, I was almost too late.

260
00:20:41,803 --> 00:20:43,347
Ma'am, just a moment.

261
00:20:43,430 --> 00:20:44,723
Excuse me. Sorry.

262
00:20:54,024 --> 00:20:54,941
What is it?

263
00:20:56,443 --> 00:20:57,694
You little…

264
00:21:01,114 --> 00:21:03,658
Gosh, you're a special guest from Seoul.

265
00:21:03,742 --> 00:21:06,036
You should sit in the best seat.

266
00:21:07,621 --> 00:21:08,580
Right.

267
00:21:09,206 --> 00:21:11,083
Gosh, you're so pretty.

268
00:21:16,296 --> 00:21:17,547
Look how great her figure is.

269
00:21:17,631 --> 00:21:20,634
-And she's so slim.
-She's just incredible!

270
00:21:21,134 --> 00:21:22,427
It could rain tonight,

271
00:21:23,136 --> 00:21:25,013
so close up and come early
if business is slow.

272
00:21:25,097 --> 00:21:26,848
Don't risk your lives for a few pennies.

273
00:21:26,932 --> 00:21:28,058
-Goodness. Thanks.
-Let's go.

274
00:21:31,812 --> 00:21:32,896
I'm fine.

275
00:21:32,979 --> 00:21:34,398
Me. Help me.

276
00:21:35,774 --> 00:21:37,109
Thank you.

277
00:21:37,859 --> 00:21:38,860
There we go, Sang-geum.

278
00:21:58,672 --> 00:22:01,466
Just you wait. I'll be back soon
with a detailed repair estimate.

279
00:22:02,676 --> 00:22:05,345
-Come on, sweetie.
-Yes, ma'am.

280
00:22:13,687 --> 00:22:14,771
Okay, get in.

281
00:22:17,566 --> 00:22:19,484
-Hurry up already.
-All right.

282
00:22:19,568 --> 00:22:20,902
What's with all this stuff?

283
00:22:20,986 --> 00:22:22,279
For goodness' sake.

284
00:22:22,362 --> 00:22:24,364
TO MUPO

285
00:22:25,073 --> 00:22:26,658
Here we go.

286
00:22:29,619 --> 00:22:31,538
-Oh, my gosh!
-My goodness!

287
00:22:44,634 --> 00:22:45,468
What's this?

288
00:22:46,052 --> 00:22:47,304
What is he doing?

289
00:22:47,387 --> 00:22:49,639
-Are you all right? Oh, my gosh.
-Yeah.

290
00:22:49,723 --> 00:22:51,057
My goodness.

291
00:22:51,141 --> 00:22:52,267
Geez.

292
00:22:54,060 --> 00:22:56,438
Hey! What are you doing?

293
00:22:56,521 --> 00:22:57,522
What's your deal?

294
00:23:03,111 --> 00:23:05,655
That little… Is he crazy?

295
00:23:11,953 --> 00:23:12,954
What?

296
00:23:21,963 --> 00:23:23,256
Are you trying to pick a fight?

297
00:23:25,425 --> 00:23:26,760
Look at the clock, not me.

298
00:23:28,220 --> 00:23:29,596
It's 2:07 p.m.

299
00:23:29,679 --> 00:23:31,264
You're supposed to leave at 2:10 p.m.

300
00:23:31,348 --> 00:23:33,767
Is this your first time on a local bus?

301
00:23:33,850 --> 00:23:35,310
Sometimes, we have to be flexible--

302
00:23:35,393 --> 00:23:36,811
This isn't the first time.

303
00:23:37,479 --> 00:23:39,272
And our village's meaning of "flexible"

304
00:23:39,356 --> 00:23:41,775
is when the elders
squeeze four cabbages of kimchi

305
00:23:41,858 --> 00:23:44,361
into food containers for you
instead of three.

306
00:23:44,945 --> 00:23:47,572
For a bus that comes
only twice a day with a five-hour gap,

307
00:23:48,156 --> 00:23:51,201
it seems rules matter
more than being flexible.

308
00:23:51,868 --> 00:23:53,370
Hey, that's…

309
00:23:53,453 --> 00:23:54,537
Look…

310
00:23:55,622 --> 00:23:57,374
Unbelievable!

311
00:24:02,003 --> 00:24:03,338
Fine, then.

312
00:24:04,130 --> 00:24:06,800
We'll leave at 2:10 p.m.

313
00:24:12,138 --> 00:24:13,139
I'll do it.

314
00:24:15,350 --> 00:24:16,977
Are you all right?

315
00:24:20,397 --> 00:24:22,691
-You're not hurt, are you?
-I'm fine.

316
00:24:22,774 --> 00:24:24,067
Are you all okay?

317
00:24:27,237 --> 00:24:28,321
Excuse me.

318
00:24:30,532 --> 00:24:31,533
Thank you.

319
00:24:45,338 --> 00:24:46,423
Do you have to sit here?

320
00:24:48,842 --> 00:24:49,968
What?

321
00:24:50,969 --> 00:24:51,928
PRIORITY SEAT

322
00:24:52,554 --> 00:24:53,596
Oh, my gosh.

323
00:24:54,306 --> 00:24:55,473
I'm sorry.

324
00:25:08,737 --> 00:25:10,196
Geez.

325
00:25:10,947 --> 00:25:12,741
I keep losing face in front of him.

326
00:25:16,745 --> 00:25:17,746
Yes?

327
00:25:22,125 --> 00:25:23,835
He'll be away from the farm for a while?

328
00:25:24,502 --> 00:25:26,921
It seems he knew we'd come
and avoided us on purpose.

329
00:25:29,215 --> 00:25:30,550
Still, you did great.

330
00:25:31,051 --> 00:25:32,218
All right, bye.

331
00:25:43,646 --> 00:25:45,106
PERFORMANCE REPORT FOR DAM YE-JIN

332
00:25:46,232 --> 00:25:47,650
You did a background check?

333
00:25:48,276 --> 00:25:49,361
I told you.

334
00:25:49,444 --> 00:25:51,237
I won't follow my sister's methods.

335
00:25:51,321 --> 00:25:53,823
There's something you must know.

336
00:25:55,116 --> 00:25:57,452
While going over Ms. Dam's
broadcast history,

337
00:25:57,535 --> 00:25:59,079
I noticed something strange.

338
00:25:59,913 --> 00:26:03,500
Aside from her debut broadcast,
she's never sold cosmetics.

339
00:26:03,583 --> 00:26:07,587
So why would she personally
send an offer to L'Étoile?

340
00:26:07,670 --> 00:26:10,673
I'm worried about her intentions.

341
00:26:10,757 --> 00:26:14,469
To me, it just looks like
she succeeded in launching new brands.

342
00:26:15,011 --> 00:26:17,097
Are we really looking at the same data?

343
00:26:17,806 --> 00:26:20,725
Please look at the last page, sir.

344
00:26:31,194 --> 00:26:34,155
2020 GOOD MORNING CREAM INCIDENT

345
00:26:34,239 --> 00:26:36,032
How does it feel to be at HIT?

346
00:26:36,574 --> 00:26:38,701
You mean, how does it feel
to return to HIT?

347
00:26:38,785 --> 00:26:40,703
We're allies now.

348
00:26:44,040 --> 00:26:47,919
Then, what will happen to Dam Ye-jin?

349
00:26:48,002 --> 00:26:50,547
We've crossed paths before,
so it does bother me.

350
00:26:51,131 --> 00:26:54,217
Right… You've met before.

351
00:26:55,510 --> 00:26:57,887
I'm thinking of letting her launch
L'Étoile's essence.

352
00:26:58,430 --> 00:26:59,305
L'Étoile?

353
00:27:00,223 --> 00:27:03,059
You're not putting her in charge
of cosmetics again, are you?

354
00:27:03,143 --> 00:27:06,563
It's been five years,
and you've returned too.

355
00:27:06,646 --> 00:27:09,816
The Dam Ye-jin of today
can easily pull it off.

356
00:27:09,899 --> 00:27:10,900
Hyun-ki,

357
00:27:12,110 --> 00:27:13,903
are we really allies?

358
00:27:19,451 --> 00:27:21,995
Let's have our meal next time.

359
00:27:43,266 --> 00:27:46,019
I, Song Myeong-hwa,
stake my name on this product

360
00:27:46,102 --> 00:27:47,270
and confidently recommend it.

361
00:27:47,353 --> 00:27:48,897
Our Good Morning Cream

362
00:27:48,980 --> 00:27:50,815
is safe for sensitive skin,

363
00:27:50,899 --> 00:27:54,027
and even infants and children
can use it without worry.

364
00:27:54,110 --> 00:27:56,654
Good Morning Cream,
the cream for your entire family.

365
00:27:56,738 --> 00:27:58,281
Try it out today.

366
00:28:01,075 --> 00:28:03,995
We just sold out!

367
00:28:12,712 --> 00:28:14,797
A home shopping broadcast garnered buzz

368
00:28:14,881 --> 00:28:17,634
with the appearance
of beloved actress Song Myeong-hwa.

369
00:28:17,717 --> 00:28:20,553
However, harmful substances
were found in the cream they sold.

370
00:28:20,637 --> 00:28:22,847
Numerous users
with inflammatory skin conditions

371
00:28:22,931 --> 00:28:25,934
have suffered serious side effects.

372
00:28:26,017 --> 00:28:30,063
As of today, I shall retire
from my acting career.

373
00:28:30,146 --> 00:28:31,397
Did you really use it yourself?

374
00:28:31,481 --> 00:28:34,067
-Where's the apology to the victims?
-Didn't you let people down?

375
00:28:38,821 --> 00:28:42,659
L'Étoile is a beauty brand
that was launched seven years ago

376
00:28:42,742 --> 00:28:45,203
by the globally renowned
French luxury group Desruets.

377
00:28:45,286 --> 00:28:49,165
It grew gradually at first
with perfume and color cosmetics.

378
00:28:49,249 --> 00:28:50,583
But three years ago,

379
00:28:50,667 --> 00:28:54,212
their product La Fin Essence
went viral as soon as it was launched.

380
00:28:54,295 --> 00:28:57,006
And now, L'Étoile is
the signature brand of the group.

381
00:28:57,090 --> 00:28:59,133
And its Executive Director Eric Seo--

382
00:28:59,217 --> 00:29:01,094
-I have a question.
-Yes?

383
00:29:01,177 --> 00:29:03,179
Why is his last name Seo?

384
00:29:04,305 --> 00:29:07,684
He's Korean, and his mother
got remarried to Desruets' CEO.

385
00:29:07,767 --> 00:29:10,562
By the way, Desruets' first wife
was also Korean.

386
00:29:10,645 --> 00:29:13,314
And his eldest daughter
is the Deputy CEO of L'Étoile.

387
00:29:14,774 --> 00:29:16,484
This isn't the time for gossip.

388
00:29:16,568 --> 00:29:18,570
Right, I'll continue then.

389
00:29:18,653 --> 00:29:20,363
L'Étoile's signature item, La Fin Essence…

390
00:29:20,446 --> 00:29:24,450
Dam Ye-jin, you're going
to cross the line?

391
00:29:25,076 --> 00:29:27,370
You think I didn't sell jewelry
because I couldn't?

392
00:29:28,454 --> 00:29:31,207
Welcome. It's been such a long time.

393
00:29:31,291 --> 00:29:32,166
This way, please.

394
00:29:36,421 --> 00:29:38,339
Can we secure enough stock of this

395
00:29:38,423 --> 00:29:40,633
so we can be on time
for the holidays next month?

396
00:29:40,717 --> 00:29:43,469
-Well, this is…
-It's limited edition, right?

397
00:29:44,387 --> 00:29:45,930
Well, for this one…

398
00:29:46,764 --> 00:29:49,893
Ms. Dam Ye-jin is already
going to sell it, so…

399
00:29:52,395 --> 00:29:54,230
-Dam Ye-jin?
-Yes.

400
00:29:56,232 --> 00:29:58,234
It lacks a bit of detail.

401
00:29:58,318 --> 00:29:59,694
-Yeah. The detail.
-Right.

402
00:30:00,445 --> 00:30:01,279
Over here.

403
00:30:01,988 --> 00:30:02,989
What about this?

404
00:30:03,781 --> 00:30:06,492
-Ms. Dam also picked this one…
-My mistake.

405
00:30:06,576 --> 00:30:08,036
Instead…

406
00:30:08,119 --> 00:30:08,995
This one!

407
00:30:09,078 --> 00:30:11,998
Ms. Dam picked that one as well.

408
00:30:12,957 --> 00:30:15,501
Are you kidding me?
Everything's been taken by Dam Ye-jin.

409
00:30:15,585 --> 00:30:17,211
Are you telling me to sell the scraps?

410
00:30:17,295 --> 00:30:18,630
No, of course not!

411
00:30:19,631 --> 00:30:20,465
What about that one?

412
00:30:21,257 --> 00:30:22,926
This is so adorable!

413
00:30:24,135 --> 00:30:25,762
Isn't it cute?

414
00:30:29,724 --> 00:30:31,225
This feature is cute.

415
00:30:31,309 --> 00:30:32,393
Can we get enough stock?

416
00:30:32,477 --> 00:30:35,688
Yes, Ms. Dam said the keychain
was too flashy, so she didn't pick--

417
00:30:35,772 --> 00:30:37,941
I won't sell it either then! I won't!

418
00:30:44,197 --> 00:30:45,990
It seems Ms. Dong has struck first.

419
00:30:46,074 --> 00:30:47,909
AUGUST 16, FIRST LAUNCH IN KOREA
ONLY AT HIT

420
00:30:47,992 --> 00:30:48,993
Hey.

421
00:30:49,911 --> 00:30:52,830
You said you didn't do cosmetics.
Is this about losing your slot?

422
00:30:52,914 --> 00:30:53,748
Yun-ji.

423
00:30:53,831 --> 00:30:56,626
I didn't agree to this,
so don't get so worked up.

424
00:30:56,709 --> 00:30:58,628
The date's right there.
You think I'm stupid?

425
00:31:00,004 --> 00:31:01,214
Hey.

426
00:31:02,465 --> 00:31:03,591
Is this your revenge?

427
00:31:08,137 --> 00:31:09,597
-Are you scared?
-Hey!

428
00:31:10,473 --> 00:31:11,766
What do you think you're doing?

429
00:31:13,935 --> 00:31:14,936
Ms. Dong.

430
00:31:15,019 --> 00:31:15,979
What's that ad?

431
00:31:17,397 --> 00:31:18,439
It's exactly what you see.

432
00:31:18,523 --> 00:31:19,649
But unfortunately,

433
00:31:20,274 --> 00:31:21,985
Ye-jin says she didn't agree to it.

434
00:31:29,450 --> 00:31:30,326
You can't do it?

435
00:31:32,495 --> 00:31:36,040
Are you going to stab
your colleagues in the back?

436
00:31:40,294 --> 00:31:43,756
They're still relying on you though.

437
00:31:47,135 --> 00:31:48,177
Ms. Dong.

438
00:31:55,810 --> 00:31:58,438
DAM YE-JIN

439
00:32:16,164 --> 00:32:20,043
Ms. Michelle sent these.
She said you'd love them.

440
00:32:21,836 --> 00:32:23,171
This is what my sister's like.

441
00:32:29,302 --> 00:32:31,971
Mr. Cha, pick one for me.

442
00:32:32,889 --> 00:32:33,723
Me?

443
00:32:35,266 --> 00:32:37,518
Pick anything. They're all great albums.

444
00:32:38,478 --> 00:32:41,272
What will be the first record
I listen to in Korea?

445
00:32:41,981 --> 00:32:43,024
I'm excited.

446
00:33:30,863 --> 00:33:31,697
Pardon?

447
00:33:36,327 --> 00:33:37,620
This umbrella.

448
00:33:37,703 --> 00:33:39,413
Where did you buy it?

449
00:34:23,958 --> 00:34:26,169
-It stopped.
-You're right.

450
00:34:27,670 --> 00:34:28,629
This place…

451
00:34:29,797 --> 00:34:31,424
-Do you know this place?
-Yes.

452
00:34:32,049 --> 00:34:35,386
I came here once but I forgot the name,
so I'd been searching for it.

453
00:34:36,262 --> 00:34:37,847
I can't believe I found it.

454
00:34:38,472 --> 00:34:41,309
You have to try their croissants.
They're the best I've ever had.

455
00:34:41,392 --> 00:34:42,643
I totally recommend them.

456
00:34:44,604 --> 00:34:47,982
Would you like
to have lunch here tomorrow?

457
00:34:50,359 --> 00:34:51,360
Sounds good.

458
00:34:52,570 --> 00:34:53,571
Good.

459
00:34:59,827 --> 00:35:00,786
Well…

460
00:35:00,870 --> 00:35:02,997
I know this might sound strange,

461
00:35:03,789 --> 00:35:05,666
but do you believe in fate?

462
00:35:06,292 --> 00:35:07,293
What?

463
00:35:09,503 --> 00:35:11,214
If you believe in fate,

464
00:35:12,673 --> 00:35:16,302
why don't we just meet here tomorrow?

465
00:36:27,999 --> 00:36:31,836
I guess you two
weren't destined to be together.

466
00:36:37,675 --> 00:36:38,509
I'm sorry.

467
00:36:40,094 --> 00:36:42,805
I thought that too, but maybe I was wrong.

468
00:36:44,473 --> 00:36:45,308
Pardon?

469
00:36:46,559 --> 00:36:48,269
I'm going to make it happen this time.

470
00:37:27,099 --> 00:37:28,476
Mechoori.

471
00:37:28,559 --> 00:37:30,061
There's a leak in the house.

472
00:37:38,778 --> 00:37:39,862
You said there was a leak.

473
00:37:39,945 --> 00:37:41,864
I wanted you to have some potatoes.

474
00:37:41,947 --> 00:37:43,449
I can't eat all this.

475
00:37:43,532 --> 00:37:44,950
Don't be so cold.

476
00:37:45,034 --> 00:37:46,827
Then, I'll just throw them away.

477
00:37:46,911 --> 00:37:47,745
Three…

478
00:37:50,081 --> 00:37:52,041
I'll just have three.
I usually skip breakfast.

479
00:37:52,124 --> 00:37:54,460
Five. I'm going to count them.

480
00:37:56,128 --> 00:37:57,296
Thank you for the food.

481
00:38:08,766 --> 00:38:12,561
Everyone, it feels like I'm walking
through a cypress forest right now.

482
00:38:13,062 --> 00:38:14,814
How should I explain this?

483
00:38:14,897 --> 00:38:16,982
Hey, isn't she that girl?

484
00:38:17,066 --> 00:38:19,693
I feel refreshed
as soon as I take a breath.

485
00:38:20,319 --> 00:38:22,613
For all of you who are busy with work…

486
00:38:22,696 --> 00:38:24,657
Is that a zero or an eight?

487
00:38:24,740 --> 00:38:26,325
…this is the perfect product.

488
00:38:26,951 --> 00:38:27,952
Look at this.

489
00:38:28,035 --> 00:38:29,954
Hey, Mechoori.

490
00:38:30,037 --> 00:38:31,288
Press the numbers for me.

491
00:38:31,372 --> 00:38:32,790
I need to buy one of those.

492
00:38:32,873 --> 00:38:36,627
The warmth spreads
through your whole body.

493
00:38:36,710 --> 00:38:39,713
Do you see all this sweat?

494
00:38:43,134 --> 00:38:46,387
What are you doing?
I have to buy it before they sell out.

495
00:38:46,470 --> 00:38:48,556
Just go to a sauna. I'll take you.

496
00:38:48,639 --> 00:38:52,017
There's no need to go to a sauna
in this hot weather.

497
00:38:52,101 --> 00:38:55,688
-Just do it comfortably at home.
-That's all exaggerated advertising.

498
00:38:55,771 --> 00:38:59,650
The 5,000 reviews on their official site
prove how effective this is.

499
00:38:59,733 --> 00:39:01,569
So I can recommend it with confidence.

500
00:39:01,652 --> 00:39:04,363
Ma'am, don't fall for such tactics
and waste your money.

501
00:39:04,447 --> 00:39:06,949
-Give it some thought.
-There's no time to think.

502
00:39:07,032 --> 00:39:10,536
Today's the last time
you'll be able to buy these at this price.

503
00:39:10,619 --> 00:39:11,662
Hurry up and order it!

504
00:39:11,745 --> 00:39:14,832
And Package 3 has just sold out.

505
00:39:16,041 --> 00:39:18,961
Your name is Yang Sang-geum, right?

506
00:39:19,044 --> 00:39:20,045
Yeah.

507
00:39:20,796 --> 00:39:23,674
-And your resident registration number?
-My ID number?

508
00:39:24,550 --> 00:39:27,136
What was it again?

509
00:39:29,346 --> 00:39:31,599
It's 470528.

510
00:39:31,682 --> 00:39:33,267
ENTER YOUR RESIDENT REGISTRATION NUMBER

511
00:39:33,350 --> 00:39:34,602
That's not it.

512
00:39:34,685 --> 00:39:37,688
Then, it must be 460528.

513
00:39:38,731 --> 00:39:39,815
That's not it either.

514
00:39:39,899 --> 00:39:43,402
Maybe 460628?

515
00:39:43,486 --> 00:39:45,362
No. Where's your ID card?

516
00:39:45,446 --> 00:39:47,656
I never use it,
so I don't know where it is.

517
00:39:49,742 --> 00:39:50,868
I'll just use my info then.

518
00:39:52,578 --> 00:39:53,871
How much should I give you?

519
00:39:53,954 --> 00:39:55,748
It's fine. This is for the potatoes.

520
00:39:57,124 --> 00:39:59,335
We'll begin the prize drawing.

521
00:39:59,418 --> 00:40:01,754
For our customers
who ordered through our mobile app,

522
00:40:01,837 --> 00:40:03,881
we'll begin a prize draw

523
00:40:03,964 --> 00:40:06,884
to win an additional bathtub.

524
00:40:09,595 --> 00:40:11,430
CONGRATULATIONS
DEOKPUNG VILLAGE, LEE * SEOK

525
00:40:11,514 --> 00:40:14,225
Mr. Lee from Deokpung Village,
Anyoung-gun.

526
00:40:14,308 --> 00:40:15,768
Congratulations.

527
00:40:18,479 --> 00:40:19,355
Deokpung Village!

528
00:40:25,486 --> 00:40:27,029
CONGRATULATIONS, LEE HAE-SEOK!

529
00:40:27,112 --> 00:40:29,365
YOU WON OUR BUY ONE, GET ONE FREE EVENT

530
00:40:33,369 --> 00:40:35,371
HIT HOMESHOPPING
DELIVERED TO YOUR DOOR WITH CARE

531
00:40:46,298 --> 00:40:47,383
Changsik.

532
00:40:48,467 --> 00:40:50,970
Changsik, why are you barking so loudly?

533
00:40:52,054 --> 00:40:53,264
Hello.

534
00:40:54,056 --> 00:40:56,642
Oh, my. Look who it is!

535
00:41:00,187 --> 00:41:03,482
Darling, I knew I'd seen you
somewhere before.

536
00:41:03,566 --> 00:41:05,568
You looked so familiar.

537
00:41:05,651 --> 00:41:07,486
I saw you were on TV.

538
00:41:09,280 --> 00:41:11,448
Wait. Let me boil you some chicken.

539
00:41:11,532 --> 00:41:12,741
No, it's fine.

540
00:41:12,825 --> 00:41:15,869
Potatoes like these
grown in rich soil with clean air

541
00:41:15,953 --> 00:41:17,830
are difficult to find in Seoul.

542
00:41:18,872 --> 00:41:21,250
By the way, what are you doing here?

543
00:41:22,126 --> 00:41:24,628
You ordered a bathtub
from our home shopping channel.

544
00:41:24,712 --> 00:41:27,298
Of course. I bought what you were selling.

545
00:41:28,090 --> 00:41:30,301
Congratulations on winning your prize!

546
00:41:31,051 --> 00:41:32,970
I won a prize?

547
00:41:33,053 --> 00:41:35,556
Yes. Your husband is Mr. Lee, right?

548
00:41:36,932 --> 00:41:41,812
Who's that? My husband's name
is Moon Gwon-pyeong.

549
00:41:43,522 --> 00:41:45,566
This was the address though.

550
00:41:45,649 --> 00:41:48,027
Then, do you know
a Mr. "Lee something Seok"?

551
00:41:48,110 --> 00:41:50,904
"Lee something Seok"? Who could that be?

552
00:41:53,782 --> 00:41:56,493
He lives way over there.

553
00:42:03,375 --> 00:42:06,211
Let's see. Go around this way and here.

554
00:42:06,295 --> 00:42:07,379
Okay, this must be it.

555
00:42:12,635 --> 00:42:15,012
Anyone home? You have a package.

556
00:42:17,640 --> 00:42:18,974
Mr. "Lee something Seok"?

557
00:42:19,058 --> 00:42:20,601
Are you home, sir?

558
00:42:20,684 --> 00:42:21,852
Mr. Lee!

559
00:42:25,648 --> 00:42:27,441
I'm not expecting any packages…

560
00:42:34,823 --> 00:42:36,659
Are you Mr. "Lee something Seok"?

561
00:42:36,742 --> 00:42:37,743
What are you doing here?

562
00:42:41,246 --> 00:42:42,581
How did you know my address?

563
00:42:43,123 --> 00:42:45,417
I'm here to deliver
Mr. "Lee something Seok" his prize.

564
00:42:45,501 --> 00:42:48,545
For privacy reasons, the middle character
of your name is hidden.

565
00:42:48,629 --> 00:42:49,713
What's your full name?

566
00:42:49,797 --> 00:42:52,424
It's Matthew. Leave it here.
I'll give it to him later.

567
00:42:53,217 --> 00:42:55,469
So your father must be
Mr. "Lee something Seok."

568
00:42:58,222 --> 00:43:02,434
Then, I guess "Mechoori"
means Matthew Lee,

569
00:43:02,518 --> 00:43:04,311
not "mechoori" as in quail.

570
00:43:06,939 --> 00:43:09,108
That's so funny. She calls you "quail"…

571
00:43:09,191 --> 00:43:11,777
MATTHEW LEE

572
00:43:11,860 --> 00:43:13,487
MECHOORI

573
00:43:15,072 --> 00:43:15,906
It's funny.

574
00:43:17,491 --> 00:43:20,911
I guess you watch my show.
You should've told me.

575
00:43:20,994 --> 00:43:22,663
If that's all, you should leave.

576
00:43:22,746 --> 00:43:26,166
I came all the way here.
I can't just go. Is your father inside?

577
00:43:28,085 --> 00:43:29,086
No, he's not.

578
00:43:31,130 --> 00:43:34,216
How come everyone
in this village is absent?

579
00:43:34,299 --> 00:43:36,218
Is everybody away on vacation or what?

580
00:43:36,301 --> 00:43:37,261
When will he come back?

581
00:43:37,344 --> 00:43:39,596
-He won't be here--
-"He won't be here for a while."

582
00:43:39,680 --> 00:43:42,141
I knew it.
That's your go-to move, isn't it?

583
00:43:42,224 --> 00:43:44,727
You said the farm owner
wouldn't be here for a while too…

584
00:43:46,061 --> 00:43:48,439
Oh, my gosh! Is your father the owner?

585
00:43:48,522 --> 00:43:50,274
No. Please, just leave now.

586
00:43:50,357 --> 00:43:52,109
Could you at least give me his number?

587
00:43:54,778 --> 00:43:56,447
Why did you come here?

588
00:43:56,530 --> 00:43:58,449
I'm here for one thing.
To meet the farm owner.

589
00:44:02,077 --> 00:44:04,329
If you're that desperate,
make an official appointment.

590
00:44:04,413 --> 00:44:05,622
Don't barge in here like this.

591
00:44:05,706 --> 00:44:07,958
Thanks for the advice,

592
00:44:08,041 --> 00:44:09,084
but instead of that…

593
00:44:12,504 --> 00:44:14,506
I'll do it my way.

594
00:44:16,800 --> 00:44:18,761
Geez, he's so cold.

595
00:44:19,470 --> 00:44:21,722
He wouldn't help me until the very end.

596
00:44:23,265 --> 00:44:25,267
But I'm never going to give up.

597
00:44:32,399 --> 00:44:34,026
I'm back.

598
00:44:35,068 --> 00:44:38,947
It's late. Have dinner before you go.
I'll boil some chicken for you.

599
00:44:39,907 --> 00:44:41,950
It's fine.
If I take a taxi, it'll be quick.

600
00:44:42,451 --> 00:44:44,787
You're taking a taxi all the way to Seoul?

601
00:44:45,496 --> 00:44:48,749
Goodness, that's a huge waste of money.

602
00:44:49,708 --> 00:44:50,876
It's really okay…

603
00:44:53,462 --> 00:44:57,716
Ma'am, do you know
the mushroom farm over there?

604
00:44:57,799 --> 00:45:01,803
Of course. I work there
and receive pay too.

605
00:45:03,805 --> 00:45:06,892
Actually, you're right.
It's kind of late to head back to Seoul.

606
00:45:06,975 --> 00:45:09,520
Is it okay if I sleep over
just for tonight?

607
00:45:23,867 --> 00:45:25,536
Goodness, what on earth?

608
00:45:25,619 --> 00:45:28,455
These little…
Come out here for a second, darling!

609
00:45:28,539 --> 00:45:30,082
Okay. Is there something wrong…

610
00:45:32,876 --> 00:45:35,045
What are you doing?
Hurry and grab the chickens!

611
00:45:35,128 --> 00:45:36,171
Yes, ma'am.

612
00:45:38,298 --> 00:45:39,925
Ma'am, I'll catch them!

613
00:45:41,260 --> 00:45:43,554
Damn it. Hey!

614
00:45:43,637 --> 00:45:45,305
Oh, my gosh. They're going nuts.

615
00:45:46,890 --> 00:45:48,976
It's trying to stop me!

616
00:45:50,310 --> 00:45:51,270
They're running.

617
00:45:53,480 --> 00:45:55,023
I'll catch them, ma'am. Damn it.

618
00:45:55,107 --> 00:45:57,150
Why are they so fast?

619
00:46:01,321 --> 00:46:02,364
Damn it.

620
00:46:07,828 --> 00:46:09,121
What?

621
00:46:11,915 --> 00:46:13,208
Hey!

622
00:46:14,251 --> 00:46:15,711
Hey! Hey, Changsik!

623
00:46:17,462 --> 00:46:18,463
Hey!

624
00:46:21,967 --> 00:46:24,761
SANG-GEUM'S CHICKEN, YE-JIN

625
00:46:24,845 --> 00:46:26,263
You're dead meat.

626
00:46:26,346 --> 00:46:27,681
Hey!

627
00:46:27,764 --> 00:46:29,308
Stop right there!

628
00:46:30,976 --> 00:46:32,060
Hey!

629
00:46:33,312 --> 00:46:35,564
Hey! Stop right there!

630
00:46:45,032 --> 00:46:46,074
I got you!

631
00:46:57,919 --> 00:46:58,754
You little…

632
00:46:59,880 --> 00:47:00,714
Hey!

633
00:47:05,052 --> 00:47:06,345
What do I do?

634
00:47:16,647 --> 00:47:17,481
Geez.

635
00:47:18,649 --> 00:47:19,524
What are you doing?

636
00:47:21,234 --> 00:47:22,611
Well, the thing is…

637
00:47:28,075 --> 00:47:30,786
Is this the way you were talking about?

638
00:47:31,828 --> 00:47:32,871
No, I…

639
00:47:32,954 --> 00:47:34,373
This is a misunderstanding.

640
00:47:34,456 --> 00:47:35,916
So…

641
00:47:35,999 --> 00:47:38,210
Ms. Yang's chicken flew over your fence

642
00:47:38,293 --> 00:47:40,170
and went into your house.

643
00:47:42,005 --> 00:47:44,216
-A chicken?
-Yes, a chicken.

644
00:47:49,471 --> 00:47:50,514
I'd like to make a report.

645
00:47:56,645 --> 00:48:00,399
Well, I looked everywhere,
but there was no trace of a chicken.

646
00:48:00,482 --> 00:48:02,150
What? That's impossible…

647
00:48:02,234 --> 00:48:06,154
I swear, the chicken
flew over the fence like this.

648
00:48:11,618 --> 00:48:12,619
Could we have a talk?

649
00:48:13,453 --> 00:48:14,287
No, thank you.

650
00:48:15,330 --> 00:48:16,707
Come on.

651
00:48:17,290 --> 00:48:18,291
Just for a second.

652
00:48:22,462 --> 00:48:23,588
What is it?

653
00:48:23,672 --> 00:48:24,756
Look.

654
00:48:26,216 --> 00:48:27,718
Do you really have to go this far?

655
00:48:28,635 --> 00:48:30,345
I'm pretty well-known.

656
00:48:30,429 --> 00:48:32,347
What if they write articles about me?

657
00:48:32,431 --> 00:48:34,141
That sounds like a meaningless concern.

658
00:48:34,224 --> 00:48:36,184
It flew over the fence?

659
00:48:36,268 --> 00:48:37,644
Maybe it dug underground.

660
00:48:40,397 --> 00:48:42,816
For now, let's go and talk at the station.

661
00:48:43,608 --> 00:48:44,901
What?

662
00:48:44,985 --> 00:48:46,695
Wait. Just a moment.

663
00:48:47,529 --> 00:48:49,823
I'm going to argue
that we're both at fault.

664
00:49:00,333 --> 00:49:03,462
Isn't a hit-and-run
a more serious offense than trespassing?

665
00:49:04,254 --> 00:49:05,547
Oh, right.

666
00:49:05,630 --> 00:49:08,049
We have experts in this field right here.

667
00:49:08,133 --> 00:49:09,217
Officers.

668
00:49:09,301 --> 00:49:10,302
Ms. Dam.

669
00:49:11,720 --> 00:49:12,721
Let's talk this over.

670
00:49:19,394 --> 00:49:21,772
You should've trusted what I said.

671
00:49:23,482 --> 00:49:24,649
How much is the repair cost?

672
00:49:28,320 --> 00:49:30,697
It's going to be at least 10 million won.

673
00:49:30,781 --> 00:49:31,740
It's limited edition.

674
00:49:34,367 --> 00:49:36,703
But I'm not that cruel.

675
00:49:36,787 --> 00:49:39,915
There's a simple and easy way
to resolve this matter.

676
00:49:40,540 --> 00:49:43,794
If you give me the farm owner's number,
I'll pretend it didn't happen.

677
00:49:43,877 --> 00:49:45,003
All right.

678
00:49:46,505 --> 00:49:47,422
What's his number?

679
00:49:47,506 --> 00:49:49,090
I'll give you the 10 million won.

680
00:49:49,674 --> 00:49:50,550
What?

681
00:49:51,301 --> 00:49:54,638
I mean, I didn't even get
a proper estimate yet.

682
00:49:54,721 --> 00:49:56,890
I don't want to be involved
in this matter anymore.

683
00:49:57,390 --> 00:49:58,600
So let's resolve it now.

684
00:50:00,268 --> 00:50:02,270
Fine. I'd be so grateful for that.

685
00:50:02,354 --> 00:50:03,480
Wait.

686
00:50:06,733 --> 00:50:07,776
Are you free for a moment?

687
00:50:08,652 --> 00:50:10,612
AGREEMENT

688
00:50:12,989 --> 00:50:15,116
Do we really have to go this far?

689
00:50:15,784 --> 00:50:17,994
Then, I'll make
an official complaint to HIT

690
00:50:18,078 --> 00:50:20,747
that their host used an event
to gain private information--

691
00:50:20,831 --> 00:50:22,415
I didn't say I wouldn't do it.

692
00:50:24,626 --> 00:50:27,671
I'm writing this clearly in big letters.

693
00:50:28,922 --> 00:50:30,215
"I, Dam Ye-jin…"

694
00:50:30,715 --> 00:50:32,092
"I, Dam Ye-jin…"

695
00:50:32,175 --> 00:50:33,343
"…promise to never…"

696
00:50:34,261 --> 00:50:36,888
-"…promise to never visit Mechoori's…"
-Matthew.

697
00:50:40,267 --> 00:50:44,437
"…promise to never visit
Matthew Lee's house again."

698
00:50:44,521 --> 00:50:46,231
-Happy?
-No. Write the address too.

699
00:50:50,026 --> 00:50:51,194
Ridiculous…

700
00:50:58,076 --> 00:51:00,328
L'Étoile keeps requesting another meeting.

701
00:51:01,746 --> 00:51:03,373
It's so annoying.

702
00:51:04,082 --> 00:51:07,043
Don't worry. I told them clearly
that we're not renewing the contract.

703
00:51:09,004 --> 00:51:10,589
Isn't it time to go home?

704
00:51:10,672 --> 00:51:13,383
Your routine's more precise
than my limited edition watch.

705
00:51:14,217 --> 00:51:16,970
Something came up, so I'm behind on work.

706
00:51:17,596 --> 00:51:18,889
Gosh, I see.

707
00:51:24,978 --> 00:51:27,147
-Let's try again.
-If you're here to say that, just go.

708
00:51:27,230 --> 00:51:30,567
See? After what the renowned L'Étoile did,
we can't trust anyone.

709
00:51:30,650 --> 00:51:33,904
Let's use these mushrooms ourselves
instead of giving them away.

710
00:51:33,987 --> 00:51:36,156
You can manage everything
from beginning to end.

711
00:51:36,239 --> 00:51:39,200
-Mu-won…
-You did what you could.

712
00:51:39,284 --> 00:51:41,786
Can't you focus
on what you've done until now

713
00:51:41,870 --> 00:51:44,080
instead of that day?

714
00:51:55,800 --> 00:51:58,970
I'm Kang Mu-won,
the guy who never gives up!

715
00:52:00,847 --> 00:52:02,641
So can't you give up instead?

716
00:52:04,267 --> 00:52:05,352
Get inside.

717
00:52:11,024 --> 00:52:12,442
These little brats.

718
00:52:14,945 --> 00:52:15,946
What a chaotic day.

719
00:52:23,328 --> 00:52:25,747
But who on earth is he though?

720
00:52:26,498 --> 00:52:27,499
A former celebrity?

721
00:52:29,584 --> 00:52:30,919
A conglomerate heir?

722
00:52:35,298 --> 00:52:37,550
No way. Is he hiding here
after committing fraud?

723
00:52:41,930 --> 00:52:43,014
No, that's not it.

724
00:52:43,098 --> 00:52:44,724
He doesn't look like a criminal.

725
00:52:44,808 --> 00:52:47,936
But otherwise, I don't see
a reason to act like that.

726
00:52:49,854 --> 00:52:51,356
What could it be?

727
00:52:57,112 --> 00:52:58,113
Hang on.

728
00:52:58,822 --> 00:53:00,824
I didn't come here to catch chickens.

729
00:53:02,575 --> 00:53:04,703
I'm not going home empty-handed this time.

730
00:53:23,013 --> 00:53:26,182
So these must be
the white flower noori mushrooms.

731
00:53:26,266 --> 00:53:28,643
They look much better in person.

732
00:53:30,729 --> 00:53:32,230
Wait!

733
00:53:32,856 --> 00:53:34,107
Come on.

734
00:53:34,190 --> 00:53:36,067
This isn't your farm.

735
00:53:36,151 --> 00:53:38,153
Earlier, we were at your house,

736
00:53:38,236 --> 00:53:41,489
but this place isn't yours,
so you can't claim any rights here.

737
00:53:41,573 --> 00:53:44,492
Even if I do get reported,
the farm owner should be doing it.

738
00:53:45,410 --> 00:53:46,619
I'm the farm supervisor.

739
00:53:47,829 --> 00:53:51,499
Come on. I already saw
the farm supervisor last time.

740
00:53:51,583 --> 00:53:55,086
If you want to chase me out,
then call the farm owner

741
00:53:55,170 --> 00:53:57,464
and tell him to come here right now.

742
00:53:57,547 --> 00:53:58,882
What do you think you're doing?

743
00:54:00,633 --> 00:54:02,010
A farm tour.

744
00:54:02,927 --> 00:54:03,928
Excuse me.

745
00:54:04,012 --> 00:54:06,931
Do you know how much
I studied about these mushrooms?

746
00:54:07,015 --> 00:54:07,932
Hey!

747
00:54:08,016 --> 00:54:11,227
They boost skin elasticity, reduce
pore size, and have antioxidant benefits.

748
00:54:12,479 --> 00:54:15,356
I knew they were amazing,
but I had to see for myself.

749
00:54:17,776 --> 00:54:18,777
Wait!

750
00:54:31,414 --> 00:54:32,582
You can't enter…

751
00:54:34,375 --> 00:54:36,920
I take back my word. Let me apologize.

752
00:54:38,463 --> 00:54:40,757
This farm isn't just amazing.

753
00:54:49,099 --> 00:54:50,141
Hang on.

754
00:54:51,518 --> 00:54:52,519
Yes?

755
00:54:53,520 --> 00:54:54,604
What?

756
00:54:55,730 --> 00:54:56,731
What is it?

757
00:55:00,443 --> 00:55:01,319
What are you doing?

758
00:55:02,445 --> 00:55:04,531
Did you just enter this farm

759
00:55:04,614 --> 00:55:05,698
carrying stuff like this?

760
00:55:05,782 --> 00:55:06,741
CHICKEN FEATHER

761
00:55:07,826 --> 00:55:10,161
Gosh, what is this doing here?

762
00:55:10,245 --> 00:55:11,079
Get out.

763
00:55:11,162 --> 00:55:12,372
But…

764
00:55:13,706 --> 00:55:14,999
There's a bug!

765
00:55:16,501 --> 00:55:18,086
Right here. And here too.

766
00:55:18,753 --> 00:55:19,796
Is this really okay?

767
00:55:19,879 --> 00:55:22,382
You shouldn't be nagging me
about hygiene right now.

768
00:55:22,465 --> 00:55:23,967
It's proof that they're organic.

769
00:55:24,050 --> 00:55:25,468
How can I believe that?

770
00:55:42,026 --> 00:55:44,821
You're interrupting my work,
so please leave.

771
00:55:52,162 --> 00:55:54,497
But why are you working late all alone?

772
00:55:55,832 --> 00:55:58,960
Do the elders make you do everything
since you're the youngest?

773
00:55:59,502 --> 00:56:00,503
Oh, dear.

774
00:56:06,718 --> 00:56:07,927
That jerk.

775
00:56:09,846 --> 00:56:11,014
Gosh, those branches…

776
00:56:32,702 --> 00:56:34,037
Don't touch the mushrooms.

777
00:56:34,120 --> 00:56:35,747
You'll lower their value.

778
00:56:36,623 --> 00:56:37,665
Yes, sir.

779
00:56:58,853 --> 00:56:59,896
What?

780
00:57:03,816 --> 00:57:05,109
When do you get off work?

781
00:57:07,612 --> 00:57:09,280
When I think I've done enough.

782
00:57:31,386 --> 00:57:34,597
I think I've done enough here too.

783
00:57:47,443 --> 00:57:48,444
Ms. Dong.

784
00:57:50,321 --> 00:57:52,407
I'll do the launch

785
00:57:53,866 --> 00:57:54,867
for L'Étoile.

786
00:58:04,627 --> 00:58:06,004
-Hello?
-Hey.

787
00:58:07,088 --> 00:58:08,172
Have you put some thought

788
00:58:08,256 --> 00:58:09,591
into our dreams and future--

789
00:58:09,674 --> 00:58:10,800
Hello?

790
00:58:10,883 --> 00:58:11,884
Hello…

791
00:58:25,315 --> 00:58:26,983
That's enough, all right?

792
00:58:27,066 --> 00:58:28,234
Hello?

793
00:58:30,570 --> 00:58:31,571
Who is this?

794
00:58:31,654 --> 00:58:32,864
Have you thought about it?

795
00:58:35,199 --> 00:58:36,117
What?

796
00:58:36,200 --> 00:58:37,994
I'm Kang Dong-koo from Gangdong-gu.

797
00:58:41,289 --> 00:58:42,123
Hey, Dong-koo.

798
00:58:42,206 --> 00:58:44,292
Tell your uncle that if he keeps this up,

799
00:58:44,375 --> 00:58:45,960
I'm changing my number.

800
00:58:47,629 --> 00:58:49,756
Hey, why would you do that? Wait!

801
00:59:56,364 --> 00:59:57,240
AGREEMENT

802
00:59:57,323 --> 01:00:00,076
I, DAM YE-JIN, PROMISE TO NEVER VISIT
MATTHEW LEE'S HOUSE AGAIN

803
01:00:10,837 --> 01:00:12,463
Moon Gwon-pyeong.

804
01:00:12,547 --> 01:00:14,215
Let's meet in my dreams.

805
01:00:16,300 --> 01:00:17,802
Are you comfortable?

806
01:00:17,885 --> 01:00:18,970
It's nice and cool, right?

807
01:00:19,679 --> 01:00:20,805
Yes, very cool.

808
01:00:22,181 --> 01:00:23,015
Goodness.

809
01:00:23,558 --> 01:00:25,435
By the way, ma'am.

810
01:00:25,518 --> 01:00:28,896
You said you work at the mushroom farm.

811
01:00:28,980 --> 01:00:31,065
Do you know the owner's number?

812
01:00:31,149 --> 01:00:32,024
His number?

813
01:00:33,151 --> 01:00:36,195
We see each other every day.
Why would I call him?

814
01:00:39,198 --> 01:00:40,199
Get some sleep.

815
01:00:40,283 --> 01:00:41,784
-Okay, good night.
-Good night.

816
01:00:42,869 --> 01:00:44,829
-Sleep tight.
-Okay.

817
01:00:52,128 --> 01:00:54,088
It's only 10:00 p.m.

818
01:01:16,486 --> 01:01:17,779
No way I'd be sleepy right now.

819
01:01:21,115 --> 01:01:22,700
This won't do.

820
01:02:09,330 --> 01:02:11,249
OWL, GRASSHOPPER,
CICADA, CRICKET, CLICK BEETLE

821
01:02:21,342 --> 01:02:22,385
FRIDAY, AUGUST 1

822
01:02:22,468 --> 01:02:23,594
It's only midnight?

823
01:02:42,613 --> 01:02:45,199
Is this for real?

824
01:03:16,606 --> 01:03:18,941
Hey, Hae-seok.

825
01:03:19,025 --> 01:03:24,614
Let's give it another try.

826
01:03:24,697 --> 01:03:26,449
Here's an acrostic. Give me the syllables.

827
01:03:27,491 --> 01:03:29,285
No, I'll do it myself.

828
01:03:29,994 --> 01:03:31,579
Lee, please, Hae-seok

829
01:03:31,662 --> 01:03:34,415
Hae, I'm begging you, Hae-seok

830
01:03:34,498 --> 01:03:36,500
Seok, you're making me upset too

831
01:03:37,627 --> 01:03:38,502
What do you think?

832
01:03:43,841 --> 01:03:46,844
CHANGE PHONE NUMBER

833
01:03:46,928 --> 01:03:48,095
YOUR NUMBER HAS BEEN CHANGED

834
01:05:07,425 --> 01:05:08,801
-Who is this--
-Mom.

835
01:05:12,304 --> 01:05:13,514
Hello?

836
01:05:13,597 --> 01:05:15,933
Mom, why weren't you picking up?

837
01:05:43,044 --> 01:05:45,921
SOLD OUT ON YOU

838
01:05:46,005 --> 01:05:51,927
THANKS TO SPECIAL GUEST AHN SANG-WOO

839
01:06:15,659 --> 01:06:17,912
You look so good together.

840
01:06:17,995 --> 01:06:19,914
I'm sorry
about yesterday's misunderstanding.

841
01:06:19,997 --> 01:06:21,582
I totally get it. Let's call it even.

842
01:06:21,665 --> 01:06:22,875
Dam Ye-jin?

843
01:06:22,958 --> 01:06:25,336
Hello, this is Dam Ye-jin,
your agent for today.

844
01:06:25,419 --> 01:06:27,505
Is this HIT?
This is how you handle things?

845
01:06:27,588 --> 01:06:29,173
I'm here today because you called me.

846
01:06:29,256 --> 01:06:30,549
Will you please leave?

847
01:06:30,633 --> 01:06:31,842
Mr. Lee!

848
01:06:34,136 --> 01:06:35,221
What was she doing here?

849
01:06:35,971 --> 01:06:38,349
You really don't recognize me?

850
01:06:38,432 --> 01:06:40,142
Let's end things with L'Étoile for good.

851
01:06:40,226 --> 01:06:42,186
You sure you won't regret it?
This is L'Étoile.

852
01:06:42,269 --> 01:06:44,021
You don't have anything to say to me?

853
01:06:44,105 --> 01:06:45,523
I hope we don't cross paths again.

854
01:06:50,027 --> 01:06:52,029
Subtitle translation by: Juyoung Park
